The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation
		 Tuesday, June 08, 2004 				 Banda brawl
																								New Delhi, June 7 (PTI): A guard at the Prime Ministers house today referred to Rajya Sabha MP Nilotpal Basu as a banda (bloke), prompting an altercation with the CPM leader. 																								Basu arrived at the Prime Ministers residence at Race Course Road for a dinner with leaders of the Congress, allies and supporting parties.																								The SPG guard who saw Basus invitation card informed his seniors on his mobile set that a banda has come for the dinner with the Prime Ministers invitation card. He asked them if Basu should be allowed in.																								The CPM leader, infuriated that an MP has been called a banda, argued with the guard till others pacified the two. 
